article.text:
==General Reference==
Home: http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/wiki/en/home

English Article Index: http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/article-index/en

==Culture and Arts==
[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-outline-of-stagecraft/outline-of-stagecraft Stagecraft]: The technical aspect of theatrical, film, and video production.

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-outline-of-chess/outline-of-chess Chess]: A two player game with a chessboard

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-outline-of-sinology/outline-of-sinology Sinology]: The study of China and things related to China.

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-newspaper/newspaper Newspaper]:  A periodical publication containing written information about current events. 

==Geography and Places==
[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-lists-of-countries-and-territories/lists-of-countries-and-territories Countries and Territories]

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-united-states/united-states United States]:  A federal republic.

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-united-kingdom/united-kingdom United Kingdom]: A federal republic.

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-france/france France]: A federal republic.

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-germany/germany Germany]: A federal republic.

==Health and Fitness==
[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-outline-of-autism/outline-of-autism Autism]: A disorder of neural development characterized by impaired social interaction and communication, and by restricted and repetitive behavior. 

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-outline-of-death/outline-of-death Death]: cessation of life.

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-outline-of-diabetes/outline-of-diabetes Diabetes]: A group of metabolic diseases in which the person has high blood glucose (blood sugar) above 200mg/dl, either because insulin production is inadequate, or because the body's cells do not respond properly to insulin, or both.

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-outline-of-the-psychiatric-survivors-movement/outline-of-the-psychiatric-survivors-movement Psychiatric Survivors Movement]: A diverse association of individuals who either currently access mental health services (known as consumers or service users), or who are survivors of interventions by psychiatry, or who are ex-patients of mental health.

==History and Events==
[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-september-11-attacks/september-11-attacks September 11 Attacks]: The September 11, 2001 attacks (also referred to as 9/11).

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-assassination-of-abraham-lincoln/assassination-of-abraham-lincoln Assassination of Abraham Lincoln]

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-world-war-iii/world-war-iii World War III]: World War III (WWIII or WW3) and the Third World War are names given to a hypothetical third worldwide large-scale military conflict subsequent to World War I and World War II. 

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-gawker/gawker Gawker]

==Human Activities==
[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-human-impact-on-the-environment/human-impact-on-the-environment Human Impact on the Environment]

==Mathematics and Logic==
[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-linearity/linearity Linearity]: Linearity is the property of a mathematical relationship or function which means that it can be graphically represented as a straight line.

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-game-theory/game-theory Game Theory]: Game theory is "the study of mathematical models of conflict and cooperation between intelligent rational decision-makers".

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-auction-theory/auction-theory Auction Theory]: Auction theory is an applied branch of economics which deals with how people act in auction markets and researches the properties of auction markets.

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-benford-s-law/benford-s-law Benford's Law]: Benford's law, also called Newcomb-Benford's law, law of anomalous numbers, and first-digit law, is an observation about the frequency distribution of leading digits in many real-life sets of numerical data.

==Natural and Physical Sciences==
[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-outline-of-biology/outline-of-biology Biology]: The natural science that involves the study of life and living organisms, including their structure, function, growth, origin, evolution, distribution, and taxonomy. 

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-outline-of-neuroscience/outline-of-neuroscience Neurosciences]: Neuroscience is the scientific study of the nervous system. It is the branch of biology that deals with the anatomy, biochemistry, molecular biology, and physiology of neurons and neural circuits. 

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-outline-of-fungi/outline-of-fungi Fungi]: "Fungi" is plural for "fungus". A fungus is any member of the group of eukaryotic organisms that includes unicellular microorganisms such as yeasts and molds, as well as multicellular fungi that produce familiar fruiting forms known as mushrooms.

==People and Self==
[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-human-rights/human-rights Human Rights]: Human rights are moral principles or norms that describe certain standards of human behavior and are regularly protected as natural and legal rights in municipal and international law.

==Philosophy and Thinking==
[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-ethics/ethics Ethics]: Ethics or moral philosophy is a branch of philosophy that involves systematizing, defending, and recommending concepts of right and wrong conduct.

==Religion and Belief Systems==
[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-outline-of-christian-theology/outline-of-christian-theology Christian Theology]: Christian theology is the study of Christian belief and practice.

[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-outline-of-spirituality/outline-of-spirituality Spirituality]: Spirituality may refer to an ultimate or an alleged immaterial reality.

==Society and Social Sciences==
[http://127.0.0.1:43110/1KiwiBCVBUcuypVm8FEmUW9YT6fJDXkN9r/?/imported/en/https-en-wikipedia-org-wiki-legality-of-bitcoin-by-country-or-territory/legality-of-bitcoin-by-country-or-territory Legality of Bitcoin]: Bitcoin is a digital currency.
